Space exploration is theologically absolutely neutral imo. If you see the sheer radicalness of the change from the original plan of pre-Fall Eden where the Incarnation would still have occurred and post-Fall procreation, predation, death, etc. any "global" change now seems small.

Basically the change between Adam and Eve's angelic life and the "current" order of Nephilim, leprosy, roses having thorns, etc. trumps any seemingly important change between lifestyles, means of sustenance, living on one continent or across the stars. It's why cosmism is a meme.
